name: Church Caelillt
description:
The church has a long history of being haunted but has always been Caelillt.

And while the air always seems uneasy, the city formed around this temple, and the Alucavous Esplanade was constructed by the servant within Caelillt.

They serve Zeus, and lightning adorns many of the signs.
note:
The origin of the name is not known, but the temple has a history of seeming haunted.

+ caeli (Air:Common)
+ illt (Evil:Dwarven)

The church actually serves Cthulu, but they use Zeus as a cover.

No worshippers of Zeus have stayed and survived, their alignment making them keen on something being wrong and the worship to the wrong god angering Cthulu himself. Also, Zeus' chaotic nature serves to hide the more evil and illicit activities of the temple.

This manifests as disappearances and an unusually high murder and crime rate for a city in Draconia that many dismiss as part of its isolationism (thus the smaller dock in the city)

name: Ancient Accuio Aquarium
description:
An underground ancient research area that served as an aquarium. Here it seems the ancients researched the optics of underwater vision and the effects of water and evolution, using it to hone arcane magics and enchantments.

Having explored it on ${"content":"318 Dormevum 24","class":"rs-lightblue"}$ <sub>${"content":"Session 36","class":"rs-darkorange"}$</sub>, you've learned this lab resides several thousand studs underground, and that a shaft protected by a yellow barrier field is the only seeming entrance. Once there it has 4 rooms:
+ A main room seemingly for conducting research and experiments.
+ A room to the north that held an ${"content":"Arcanic Channeling Staff","class":"rs-darkorange"}$ after the display panels were turned white by touching both with red, green, and blue power crystals and expending a red crystal to a red glowing panel in the laboratory.
+ A room to the east that holds a pure black box that omits no light and seems to pull at near by power crystals. The lone glass pane floating in the room seems to prompt to do something with a power crystal, responding to red, green, and blue crystals with an intricate arcane sigils in a very complex arcane circle.
+ A room to west that has several floating glass panes that various combinations of power crystals resulted in an alarm, that, after everyone left every room, resulted in the lab going into some form of lock down.

More exploration seems needed, but several power crystals were consumed during the exploration, so more should be acquired before returning, particularly of the red and green variety as those were the colors consumed. Others may be needed as well.

Peum is a religious city founded around the Church Caelillt, which has reside there for several centuries.

Over the last few decades it has grown quite a bit, many giving thanks to Ixeba Ratabu for its growth and his political sway to convince people to come.

Another is the beautiful Alucavous Esplanade, that offers a protected beautiful park to stroll through.

It's remote location and semi-isolationist stance on many political topics has made it an ideal refuge for those who wish to avoid the outside world. As a large provider of food to the Draconian empire, it is also well suited to feeding those refuges as well.
note:
This city also serves as the main perch for Cthulu in the world. While diminished from the apocalypse millennia ago, his followers have kept him strong here through rituals and sacrifice and a great deal of magical showmanship to hide it all.

The instability of the island however made metal the prime candidate even with this as a factor, leading to some creative ways of preventing rust from forming. At its height, while still suffering from rust issues, the city drew a number of tourists and its port served many boats from all the nations as an easy resting point between the seas. This however, as a leoterran city,it also made it an important tactical point, lead to its quick fall at the start of the war between Leoterra and Nautregno.
